Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim and peel @Carrots{4}; cut on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces.

Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}, @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season generously with salt and pepper; drizzle with olive oil.

Once carrots have roasted for 5 minutes, remove from oven.

Add chicken to opposite side of sheet from carrots. Continue roasting until chicken is cooked through and carrots are tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of salt.

Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Once chicken is cooked through, remove sheet from oven; transfer carrots to a plate.

Heat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees.

Spread half the @Pesto{2%ounce} onto tops of chicken, then sprinkle with @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup}.

Return to top rack and broil or bake until cheese is melty, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} and lemon zest to taste.

Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice, chicken, and carrots between plates.

Sprinkle with as many @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like.

Serve with lemon wedges and remaining pesto on the side for dipping.